remodeling. Treatment with GLP-1R agonists in both humans and rodents mitigates glial polarization and neuroinﬂammation. The induction of an anti-inﬂam-
matory state reduces vascular damage and neuronal loss and increases tight junction expression, pericyte coverage, and insulin-induced cerebrovascular
relaxation. GLP-1 treatment upregulates the expression of VEGF and induces vascular plasticity in cerebrovascular diseases such as CIRI and TBI.
ll
